Prime Minister Arseniy Yatsenyuk of Ukraine will visit the White House on March 12. The purpose of the visit is to show strong support for the people of Ukraine who have displayed courage during times of crisis. President Obama and Prime Minister Yatsenyuk will discuss finding a peaceful solution to Russia's military intervention in Crimea while respecting Ukrainian sovereignty. They will also talk about international support for Ukraine's economic challenges and the importance of uniting the country and fulfilling the aspirations of its people in preparation for the upcoming presidential elections in May.